@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<div class="container mt-4">
    <h1 class="mb-3">@ViewData["Title"]</h1>

    <p class="text-muted">
        Last updated: @DateTime.UtcNow.ToString("MMMM dd, yyyy")
    </p>

    <p>
        Thank you for using Charr & Challaw ordering website. We value your trust and are committed 
        to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains what data we collect, 
        how we use it, and the choices you have regarding your information.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Information We Collect -->
    <h3>1. Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>We collect information to provide a smooth ordering experience. This includes:</p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Account Information</strong> – Name, email address, and password when you register.</li>
        <li><strong>Order Information</strong> – Items ordered, pickup name, phone number, and notes.</li>
        <li><strong>Automatic Data</strong> – Basic technical information sent by your browser, such as:
            <ul>
                <li>IP address</li>
                <li>Browser type</li>
                <li>Device information</li>
                <li>Pages visited</li>
            </ul>
        </li>
        <li><strong>Cookies & Session Data</strong> – Used to store your shopping cart and keep you signed in.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Use of Information -->
    <h3>2. How We Use Your Information</h3>

    <p>We only use your data to operate and improve our service. This includes:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Processing food orders and payments.</li>
        <li>Managing your cart and checkout session.</li>
        <li>Account authentication and login security.</li>
        <li>Improving website performance and user experience.</li>
        <li>Sending order confirmations or pickup updates.</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        <strong>We do NOT sell or share your personal information</strong>
        with advertisers or outside companies.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Sharing of Information -->
    <h3>3. When We Share Information</h3>

    <p>We only share your information in limited, necessary cases:</p>

    <ul>
        <li><strong>Service Providers</strong> – Such as secure web hosting platforms.</li>
        <li><strong>Legal Requirements</strong> – If required by law or to protect our rights.</li>
        <li><strong>Internal Staff</strong> – Admin or staff may view order details to prepare food.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Cookies -->
    <h3>4. Cookies & Local Storage</h3>

    <p>Our website uses cookies to provide features such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Shopping cart storage</li>
        <li>User authentication</li>
        <li>Keeping you logged in between visits</li>
    </ul>

    <p>You may disable cookies in your browser settings, but some website functions may stop working.</p>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Data Security -->
    <h3>5. Data Security</h3>

    <p>
        We use modern security practices to protect your information.  
        However, no system can be 100% secure. Always use a strong, unique password on your account.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Your Choices -->
    <h3>6. Your Choices & Rights</h3>

    <p>You may:</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Update your account information at any time.</li>
        <li>Delete your account by contacting us.</li>
        <li>Request a copy of your account or order data.</li>
        <li>Opt out of non-essential communications.</li>
    </ul>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Children's Privacy -->
    <h3>7. Children's Privacy</h3>

    <p>
        This website is not intended for children under 13.  
        We do not knowingly collect information from minors.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Changes to This Policy -->
    <h3>8. Changes to This Policy</h3>

    <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.  
        Updates will be posted on this page with a new “Last Updated” date.
    </p>

    <hr />

    <!-- SECTION: Contact -->
    <h3>9. Contact Us</h3>

    <p>If you have questions about this policy or need help with your data, you may contact us:</p>

    <p>
        <strong>Email:</strong> support@charrandchallaw.local<br />
        <strong>Phone:</strong> (555) 123-4567
    </p>

    <p class="text-muted small">
        This privacy policy is provided for educational and demonstration purposes.
    </p>
</div>
